pageContext.claim: “Many mostly Democrat States refused to hand over data from the 2016 Election to the Commission On Voter Fraud.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump, as usual, goes too far to pin the resistance to providing the data on “mostly Democrat States.” There is a Democratic tilt to the opposition, especially if one assumes the states requesting payment might have eventually provided data. But a relatively large percentage of Republican-leaning states also did not provide data.
